EAN, and should also ensure it handles kind=MEAN's requirements (we could also dispatch differently, but the best fix would be in mplhep) CC @andrzejnovak\r\n* Boost-histogram should describe accumulators/storages a bit more in the docs, especially setting with a stack, including the correct order. CC Me\r\n\r\nIf kind=MEAN, you are only supposed to plot variances if `counts() > 1`, and values if `counts() >= 1`.\r\n", "created_at": "2021-03-18T22:06:08Z", "updated_at": "2021-04-09T21:19:42Z", "closed_at": "2021-04-09T16:56:08Z", "merged_at": "2021-04-09T16:56:08Z", "merge_commit_sha": "b2fdc01ac98e4c8eba56f6acf34f5c28fd79866e", "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [], "milestone": null, "draft": false, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/hist/pulls/160/commits", "review_comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/hist/pulls/160/comments", "review_comment_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/hist/pulls/comments{/number}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/hist/issues/160/comments", "statuses_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/hist/statuses/92d0da9c46459920c4b355529a8b7ab39647227f", "head": {"label": "scikit-hep:feat/profile", "ref": "feat/profile", "sha": "92d0da9c46459920c4b355529a8b7ab39647227f", "user": {"login": "scikit-hep", "id": 23454624, "node_id": "MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjIzNDU0NjI0", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/23454624?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep", "html_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/subscriptions", "o